Center: Center of Nuclear Physics Data, Russian Federal Nuclear Center (VNIIEF), Sarov, Russia
title: The (d,a) reaction on N-15 and O-16 in the deuteron energy range 1-2.5 MeV.

x4freetext: The (d,a) reaction on N-15 and O-16 in the deuteron
energy range 1-2.5 MeV.
The 2.5 MeV electrostatic accelerator.
Two n-semiconductor detectors were placed
inside the scattering chamber, a fixed one used as a
monitor was mounted at an angle 135 degr. with respect
to the beam while the other could be rotated from 30 to
150 degr.
The absolute differential
cross section for the measured alpha groups was
calculated on the one hand by normalizing to the
current integrator reading and on the other hand by
normalizing to the well-known value for the
14N(d,a)12C cross section at the same energy.
Nitrogen gas enriched to 96% 15N was used as a target.
The gas pressure inside the chamber was such that the
target thickness did not exceed 10 keV at Ed=2.0 MeV.
For an oxygen target the chamber was filled with air at
the same pressure. The effective target thickness was
determined by the diameter of the last diaphragm and
the width of the slip placed in front of the alpha
particle counter. To decrease the beam divergence the
last diaphragm was placed 2 cm from the centre of the
chamber.
